19 SUMMARY
2260 This resolve requires the Maine State Housing Authority to enter into negotiations to
2271 purchase the land and buildings located in the City of Bangor commonly known as the
2282 Bangor Mall. If, within 12 months of the effective date of this resolve, a purchase and sale
2293 agreement, or other contract for the purchase of the Bangor Mall has not been executed by
3204 all necessary parties, the Maine State Housing Authority is required to exercise its right of
3215 eminent domain to acquire the Bangor Mall. Within 6 months of acquiring the Bangor
3226 Mall, the Maine State Housing Authority is required to submit a report to the joint standing
3237 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing matters detailing the costs
3248 of converting the Bangor Mall into affordable housing units and proposing legislation to
3259 create the Bangor Mall Housing Authority. The area of operation of the Bangor Mall
3360 Housing Authority must be limited to the area of property conveyed to or taken by the
3371 Maine State Housing Authority under this resolve, and the area of operation of any
3382 municipal housing authority in the City of Bangor excludes this area. The resolve
3393 appropriates $25,000,000 to the Maine State Housing Authority for the purchase and
4304 improvement of the Bangor Mall.
